Ministry of Defence 1 was a weapons laboratory set up in 1939 by Winston Churchill . 
  He was a firm believer in the importance of science and technology in warfare . 
  Some of his inventions were so successful they played a vital role in ending World War Two . 
  The panjandrum was a giant wheel covered in rockets  . 
  The Atlantic Wall was a series of fortifications built to protect against Allied invasion  . 
  The ‘human torpedo’ was a device used to attach explosives to ships  . 
 